\par\par \b \uc2  GOVERNMENT ASKED TO MONITOR CURRENT ACCOUNT  \highlight22\uc2 DEFICIT \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 496 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 January 1995\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  9 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1995 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Members of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  urged the government yesterday to closely monitor the country's widening current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  and mounting foreign debt. \par \par \uc2  The request, made in the wake of last week's run on the rupiah, was made during the first round of the deliberation of the 1995-96 draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The Indonesian Democratic Party's faction in the House warned that the current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  could become a serious problem in the next \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year if no concrete measures were taken. \par \par \uc2  "The country's balance of payments should be closely monitored as the expected surge in imports resulting from the increase in new investments could further worsen the country's current account performance," the faction's spokesman, Soedaryanto, told the House's plenary session, which was attended by Minister of Finance Mar'ie Muhammad. \par \par \uc2  Foreign fund managers dumped the rupiah last week, fearing that a Mexican-style devaluation might also take place in Indonesia. The Mexican financial crisis also rocked other emerging markets, including Malaysia, the Philippines and Thailand. \par \par \uc2  The Indonesian Democratic Party estimated that the current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  might exceed the projected level if no appropriate steps were taken to curb imports and mounting foreign debt, and to improve the competitiveness of the country's non-oil exports. \par \par \uc2  The current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  is projected to further expand to US$4.09 billion in 1995-96 from the estimated $3.56 billion this \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year and $2.94 billion in 1993-94. \par \par \uc2  The government said that the current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , accounting for 2.3 percent of the country's gross domestic product, is still at a safe level. \par \par \uc2  Minister Mar'ie said that the country's foreign debt, totaling around US$93 billion as of September last year, was not a cause for alarm, given the large capacity of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Fears \par \par \uc2  Soedaryanto said that the government had to take concrete steps to allay fears about a possible devaluation, as issuing promises would not be sufficient. \par \par \uc2  The Moslem-dominated United Development Party's (PPP) faction also stressed the need for a more prudent \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in managing the balance of payments and the country's foreign account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The PPP shared the Indonesian Democratic Party's view about the need for closer control of foreign debt and import activities as the worsening of those two \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals could undermine the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability. \par \par \uc2  The PPP faction's spokesman, Mukrom As'ad, said that the rise in the country's foreign debt, estimated to reach $100 billion in the next \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, should be curbed as the prospects of the country's exports could become more \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the future. \par \par \uc2  "If we fail to improve the competitiveness of our products, we will become a loser in the world market," he said of the need to improve the quality of local products in the face of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  globalization. (hen) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1995 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011103dr1i008kg\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
