\par\par \b \uc2  SOUND MONETARY POLICIES VITAL FOR FIRM EXCHANGE RATE. \b0\par\par\uc2 565 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 April 1995\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  10 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1995 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  NUSA DUA, Bali (JP): Businesspersons meeting over the weekend, under the APEC Financiers Group, saw sound \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary policies as one of the primary conditions to secure a stable currency market. \par \par \uc2  "We all agree that governments should pursue sound \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary policies, with sustainable current account deficits to secure a stable global monetary system," Toyoo Gyohten, chairman of the Bank of Tokyo, said. \par \par \uc2  Robert D. Hormats, vice chairman of Goldman Sachs, specifically called on the Japanese government to further deregulate its market and the United States government to reduce its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  and increase its savings rate. \par \par \uc2  The two businessmen made the remarks at a news conference at the end of the first meeting of the APEC Financiers Group at the Bali Inter-Continental Resort, which was hosted by Lippobank and the Indonesian Private National Banking Association (Perbanas). \par \par \uc2  APEC (Asia Pacific \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Cooperation forum) groups Australia, Brunei, China, Canada, Chile, Hong Kong, Indonesia, Japan, Malaysia, Mexico, New Zealand, Papua New Guinea, the Philippines, Singapore, South Korea, Taiwan, Thailand and the United States. \par \par \uc2  Perbanas' Chairman Trenggono Purwosuprodjo said the meeting was held to implement the recommendation of the first APEC finance ministers' meeting in Honolulu, Hawaii, in March, 1994. \par \par \uc2  The Honolulu meeting called for the formation of a financiers group of private financial sector leaders to convene a meeting to identify issues regarding capital market development, to explore ways to strengthen private sector contacts and the possibility of establishing a more permanent private sector structure. \par \par \uc2  Recommendations \par \par \uc2  "We have suggested several recommendations to the APEC finance ministers, who are holding their second annual meeting at the Grand Bali Beach, regarding infrastructure financing, capital market development and effective financial market environments," Trenggono said. \par \par \uc2  Trenggono said the meeting, attended by 38 bankers and businessmen from 13 out of the 18 APEC members, did not include the exchange rate volatility in the official agenda. \par \par \uc2  "But since all of us have been affected by the excessive currency swings, notably the Japanese yen and the dollar, that issue popped up in discussions between the participants," he added. \par \par \uc2  Gyohten noted that exchange rate volatility discouraged cross border capital flows because such \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  increased the risks of investments. \par \par \uc2  "Therefore, I think, there should be a stronger international cooperation to remove the currency volatility," the Japanese banker added. \par \par \uc2  Another businessman from Singapore observed that the price \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  caused by currency swings would affect especially long-term investments, which are badly needed by APEC members to develop their infrastructure. \par \par \uc2  He said exchange rate gyrations also increased the risks and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in international transactions and depressed the supply of exports and the demand for imports. \par \par \uc2  Hormats said that since the impact of the yen-dollar misalignment was quite significant on international business transactions, it was high time for both countries to act together in a more concerted manner to cope with the problem. \par \par \uc2  "I think further deregulation of the Japanese market would be quite helpful," he added. \par \par \uc2  The United States in turn should work harder to reduce its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  and to increase its savings rate, the American investment banker added. \par \par \uc2  Businesspeople from the developing countries seemed to bear a greater brunt of the exchange rate volatility because most of them, notably the medium and small-scale ones, do not have the resources, adequate networks, to hedge against exchange rate risks. (vin) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1995 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011103dr4h007bu\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
