\par\par \b \uc2  GOVT ROLE NEEDED IN  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMIC \highlight\uc2  DEREGULATION. \b0\par\par\uc2 448 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 June 1995\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  10 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1995 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The process of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  liberalization in developing countries needs their governments' roles through \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  planning to ensure that it will run well, without instigating destabilization, economist Dorodjatun Kuntjoro-Jakti says. \par \par \uc2  "The functions of governments' \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  planning are not only for \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  and nationalization processes, but also for deregulation and privatization advances," Dorodjatun said at a ceremony for his promotion as a new professor in the School of Economics of the University of Indonesia on Saturday. \par \par \uc2  Dorodjatun said that in the current era of globalization, the role of governments through \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  planning remains a strategic element of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development processes. \par \par \uc2  He presented five arguments on the importance of governments' touch on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development planning. He described the five reasons as follows. \par \par \uc2  . Development is not an instantaneous and/or automatic process. It needs stimulators and a long time to experience changes in different stages. Governments' roles through their \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies are needed to maintain the continuity and consistency of development process. \par \par \uc2  . Development goes on not without funds and side effects. In terms of dislocation of funds, particularly when it creates negative impacts such as unemployment, governments have to hastily intervene to avoid instability, which can disrupt the continuity of the development. \par \par \uc2  . Knowledge about development has been largely accumulated, which results in the emergence of a common view in the process of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development. With such accumulated knowledge, governments could identify any deviation of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development at the very early stage, and thus they can correct the deviation quickly. \par \par \uc2  . The modern \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , especially in the era of information, is full of data, information and sciences. The governments, with their large bureaucratic networks, can provide all of them. The macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , therefore, will remain a specialty of governments. \par \par \uc2  . Globalization brings about many quantum leaps, which will, sooner or later, result in discontinuities. To anticipate all \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , governments should reduce the risks for the sake of the continuity of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities. \par \par \uc2  Success \par \par \uc2  However, Dorodjatun noted that the success requirements of the liberalization process are difficult to meet, especially by developing countries. \par \par \uc2  Success conditions include professional government officials, governments' strong political supports for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  liberalization, national consensus on ways to liberalize the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the availability of accurate data and information to support the liberalization process. \par \par \uc2  "Looking at the four success requirements, it can be predicted that many developing countries will not be able to counter the incessant globalization onslaughts," Dorodjatun said. \par \par \uc2  He noted that the Indonesian government's role in the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  planning is vital, to ensure that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  liberalization will not lead to a laissez faire, or an etatism, or a free fight liberalism. (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1995 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011103dr6j0099c\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
