\par\par \b \uc2  END OF BI SWAP FACILITIES WON'T AFFECT FOREX MART. \b0\par\par\uc2 669 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 July 1995\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1995 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's move yesterday to end its foreign exchange swap facilities for the banking industry is not expected to have any major impact on the foreign exchange market. \par \par \uc2  Rusli Suryadi, the vice president of Bank Bali, said that the impact of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's move would be insignificant because the larger part of swap transactions already take place outside the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  system. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  abolished, beginning yesterday, swap facilities for the banking industry in a move to give commercial banks a greater role in foreign exchange dealing. \par \par \uc2  "In the long-term, yes, especially when there is an unexpected event in the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Rusli told The Jakarta Post. of the possible speculative impact of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's move on foreign exchange dealing. \par \par \uc2  He said that the abolition of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's swap facilities was in line with the globalization trend in the financial sector. \par \par \uc2  Rusli said the decision was also a natural consequence of the greater role being played by commercial banks in foreign exchange trading. \par \par \uc2  He said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's swap facilities are, in fact, no longer popular among banks because of their high premium rates, which are approximately one to two percentage points above those charged on inter-bank transactions. \par \par \uc2  "It is, therefore, natural for the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to end the facilities," he said. \par \par \uc2  The premium rates charged by \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the swap facilities for six-month maturity was around 10.75 percent per annum last week, as compared with roughly nine percent charged by commercial banks for similar facilities. \par \par \uc2  A foreign exchange dealer at a foreign bank said that the short-term impact of the abolition of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's swap facilities was likely to be minimal. \par \par \uc2  Rupiah \par \par \uc2  The source, who requested anonymity, acknowledged that a number of Singapore-based investment fund managers had bought more rupiah early yesterday in anticipation of an increase in the value of the rupiah as a result of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's move. \par \par \uc2  "But their maneuver received no response from the market and they then released their rupiah in the afternoon," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said that speculative trading, as a side effect of the freer swap system, would take place only when there was \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  regarding the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , such as when there was a sharp drop in the price of oil, Indonesia's major export earner. \par \par \uc2  He added, however, that in such exceptional conditions the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be ready to reintroduce the facilities or take similar action to curb speculation. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  introduced swap facilities in 1979 to help commercial banks hedge the foreign loans of their customers from a possible sharp fall in the value of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said in a statement over the weekend that the government's commitment to adopt a more market-oriented system had significantly reduced the dominance of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's foreign exchange activities in the last 10 years. \par \par \uc2  The swap transactions of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , for example, dropped sharply to US$1 billion last year from over $13 billion in 1971 as a result of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's more market-oriented policies, the statement said. \par \par \uc2  By contrast, it said, the swap transactions carried out by commercial banks had sharply increased to $85 billion from $29 billion during the same period. \par \par \uc2  Banking analysts said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's move to give commercial banks more independence was timely. \par \par \uc2  Rijanto, a noted local banking analyst, said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's move would discourage commercial banks from raising offshore funds because a large amount of foreign exchange would no longer receive significant protection in the absence of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's swap facilities. \par \par \uc2  He said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's move could also cause an increase in the swap premium rates on inter-bank transactions, which at present range between six and nine percent per annum. (hen) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1995 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011103dr7i005dz\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
