\par\par \b \uc2  SECTARIAN CONFLICT REAL THREAT TO UNITY - EDI. \b0\par\par\uc2 614 \uc2 words\par \uc2 26 July 1995\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1995 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  SEMARANG (JP): Social problems generated from ethnic, religious and inter-group conflict are becoming a real threat to the nation's unity, Minister of Defense and Security Gen. (ret) Edi Sudrajat warns. \par \par \uc2  Edi said the increasing coverage in the mass media on worries about the ongoing sectarian trend shows that the threat is no longer an illusion. \par \par \uc2  "It will be wrong to think that the issue is fabricated by the ABRI (Armed Forces)," Edi said when addressing a congress of the Association of Indigenous Entrepreneurs (HIPPI) on Monday night. \par \par \uc2  The minister said that issues related to ethnicity, religion and social groups remain highly sensitive in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  "It is indeed inconvenient to openly discuss the issues but the problem will linger as long as we do not try to resolve it," he told about 400 participants of the congress. \par \par \uc2  Edi's warning on similar dangers was the second he made over the past week. Earlier last week, he said that bankers' favoritism of wealthy ethnic Chinese businessmen, in issuance of credit, may worsen social envy. \par \par \uc2  In a country of 185 million people, where the gulf between the rich and the poor is widening, the dominant role of ethnic Chinese entrepreneurs in \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is increasingly under scrutiny. \par \par \uc2  On Monday, HIPPI supervisory board chairman Probosutedjo charged in the congress that Indonesia's entrepreneurs of foreign descent are "less nationalistic", for instance they often threaten to shift their investment overseas if they are not given privileges at home. \par \par \uc2  Edi stressed on Monday on the need to strengthen national unity, so that the nation will be strong enough to repulse problems which may have disintegrative impacts. \par \par \uc2  He pointed out that one way to improve national stability is to strengthen the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  resilience. \par \par \uc2  He said that Indonesia should work hard to make its \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  solid enough to face the negative impact of the oncoming world trade liberalization. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia means to develop an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  system in which the weak can survive because the strong businesses cannot take it all, like one which is commonly practiced in the West. \par \par \uc2  "To achieve the goal, Indonesian businesses should always have in mind things like equal distribution of state wealth, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  disparity and social envy. In other words, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development and empowerment of the poor should go hand in hand," Edi said. \par \par \uc2  The minister also urged HIPPI members to become independent and not rely on facilities from the government. "A true entrepreneur is characterized by his ability to grab a business opportunity and never take the shortcut by trampling on business ethics and violating laws." \par \par \uc2  He acknowledged that small-scale entrepreneurs will be difficult to grow if the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is still dominated by a certain group and if legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  prevails. \par \par \uc2  The government should also play a more active role in creating a condition conducive for all businesses to grow on equal footing, he said. Bureaucrats should ease administrative procedures often seen as a barrier to business development. \par \par \uc2  Edi also called on the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  not to politicize the raging debate on the businesses of government officials' offsprings. \par \par \uc2  "The debate should be interpreted as a reflection of people's wish to create equal business opportunities for all," he said. \par \par \uc2  The debate on the business interests of government officials' was started recently by members of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , who want clear-cut regulations on that particular issue. \par \par \uc2  Critics say that officials' children's lack professionalism in doing their business and rely on government facilities at the cost of "ordinary" entrepreneurs. \par \par \uc2  Others say that there is nothing wrong with officials' children doing business as long as they do not abuse their parents' power. (har/pan) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1995 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011103dr7q001w9\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
