\par\par \b \uc2  GOVT TO MAINTAIN PRUDENT MONETARY,  \highlight22\uc2 FISCAL \highlight\uc2  POLICIES. \b0\par\par\uc2 750 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 August 1995\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  9 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1995 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Minister of Finance Mar'ie Muhammad pledged to maintain prudent monetary and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies to anticipate and face global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  trends. \par \par \uc2  "To face the global changes and challenges, we need to continue and enhance a prudent, or even a very prudent approach in managing our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , including \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary affairs," Mar'ie said in his speech at Airlangga University's 41st anniversary in Surabaya, East Java, on Saturday. \par \par \uc2  Mar'ie noted that by taking an extra-prudent approach, it does not mean that Indonesia takes a passive, static or even stagnant approach to its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  management. "This extra-careful approach will make us always ready to face the worst condition ever." \par \par \uc2  As world \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  trends move very quickly and are very transparent, liberal and full of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Indonesia needs to closely monitor and anticipate the trends and continuously adapt its \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to the trends, especially those prevailing in its prime trade partners. \par \par \uc2  He warned that any instability in the world's leading economies would affect other economies, especially the developing ones. Mexico's monetary crisis early this year, which almost dragged other emerging economies, including Indonesia, into another crisis, serves as a good example. \par \par \uc2  "Indonesia was successful in avoiding the negative impact of the Mexican crisis by minimizing speculations," Mar'ie said. "This success was closely related to the condition of our \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals, the government's quick reaction to the crisis and the business sector's trust in our \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary authority." \par \par \uc2  Mar'ie said that prudent \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary policies should be followed by efficient management on the side of the "real" sectors. "To make our national development programs a success story, it needs strong and sustainable coordination between the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary sectors." \par \par \uc2  He noted that the direction of Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary policies would be much influenced by the private sectors, both domestic and overseas, which had been contributing a large portion of investment funding in the country. \par \par \uc2  Efficiency \par \par \uc2  "Therefore, any inefficiency on the part of the private sector will seriously affect our efficiency record on the national level," the minister said. \par \par \uc2  He said that to improve the country's efficiency, the government would continue bringing down the remaining high tariffs, to a level of a maximum of 10 percent by 2003, when the agreement on the ASEAN Free Trade Area is fully implemented. \par \par \uc2  The Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam. \par \par \uc2  Mar'ie said the government is also gradually removing non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  barriers and changing them into \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  barriers, as required by the World Trade Organization, of which Indonesia is amember. \par \par \uc2  "However, it needs to be noted here that a number of developed countries are introducing new non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  barriers, which were previously not recognized both in practice and in theory. They are like those related to eco-labeling, as well as labor wages, which they consider as disguised \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Mar'ie said. \par \par \uc2  The minister then explained long-term prudent \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary policies, which are expected to be adaptive to global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  trends. The policies include: \par \par \uc2  * Maintaining the concept of balanced and dynamic budgeting and improving the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  discipline, both on the earning and the \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  sides. On the earning side, the government will consistently enhance domestic revenues, especially those from \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and other sectors. On the \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  side, it is necessary to minimize the leaking of the funds and unnecessary \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  * Taking a contractive budgeting \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to reduce inflationary pressures and avoid the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  from overheating. The growth of money supply and bank credits is maintained at a safe level. \par \par \uc2  * Maintaining the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of floating exchange rates to safeguard Indonesia's currency stability, as well as improve the competitiveness of Indonesia's export commodities. \par \par \uc2  * Continuing efforts to reduce the current account deficits by encouraging more non-oil exports, as well as deficits in trade of services. \par \par \uc2  * Improving the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 's savings, to reduce the country's dependence on foreign debts. To reduce its foreign debt burdens, especially those with high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government can sell its healthy state firms on overseas stock markets. \par \par \uc2  * Encouraging the private sectors to generate funds from stock markets, either local or overseas exchanges, to slow down the incoming rate of the private sectors' foreign debts. \par \par \uc2  * Continuing deregulatory measures, to further cut the country's import \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  levels and remove non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  barriers to improve Indonesia's global competitiveness. (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1995 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011103dr8f002j8\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
