\par\par \b \uc2  NEW LAWS NEEDED TO CUT HIGH-COST  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMY \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 637 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 May 1996\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1996 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Indonesia needs to enact new laws on \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and levies imposed by local administrations and on non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue resources administered by the central government in order to reduce the high-cost components of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  Director General Fuad Bawazier said yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Fuad told a seminar organized by the Center for \b \highlight22\uc2 Fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Monetary Studies that the proposed two laws would serve as a starting point to restructure the numerous levies which have been blamed for both the high cost of doing business in the country and the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  inefficiency. \par \par \uc2  "Those laws would provide legal certainty for ministries and local administrations as well as the people, in this case businesspeople," Fuad told the seminar,. \par \par \uc2  He noted that legal levies, called retributions, and local \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  have created \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the business community because the collection of these levies and \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  often created illegal levies. \par \par \uc2  Fuad noted that since Law No.11/1957 on local \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Law No.12/1957 on local retributions are no longer enforced, the levying and collection of local \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and retributions had turned into a jungle without clear-cut rules. \par \par \uc2  "It is now difficult to distinguish local \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  from retributions. Levies are imposed often without any consideration as to their social and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  cost," he pointed out. \par \par \uc2  Very often such levies cause distortions in the allocation of resources and even welfare losses as their collection costs are sometimes higher than the revenues collected, Fuad said. \par \par \uc2  "Many local administrations do not realize this because it is the central government that pays the salaries of most local officials, including those who collect the levies," he added. \par \par \uc2  According to the National Development Planning Board (Bappenas), there are five kinds of \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and 58 kinds of retributions collected by provincial administrations. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, in each district administration, Bappenas recorded 36 kinds of \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and 134 different retributions. \par \par \uc2  Fuad argued, however, that only a few of the retributions, both at the provincial and district levels, have the potential to generate significant revenues. \par \par \uc2  User \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Soemarso, chairman of the Center for \b \highlight22\uc2 Fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Monetary Studies - the research arm of the Yayasan Bina Pembangunan foundation - suggested that the government allow ministries and other state institutions to generate their own funding by imposing user \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "By doing so, state institutions could achieve a self-financing capability and would be able to give better remuneration to their employees and eventually better services to the people," Soemarso said. \par \par \uc2  Participants at the seminar, including members of the House Budgetary Commission, criticized the unbalanced \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  authority between the central government and local administrations. \par \par \uc2  They blamed the proliferation of levies in the provinces and districts on the requirement for local administrations to increase their self-financing capability. \par \par \uc2  "This requirement has forced local administrations to impose levies or retributions because almost all \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  related to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities are administered by the central government," noted Aberson Marle Sihaloho, deputy chairman of the House Budgetary Commission. \par \par \uc2  Aberson blamed the government for not supplementing Law No.5/1974 on regional autonomy with a law on \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  balance between the central government and local administrations because the previous \b \highlight22\uc2 legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2  (Law No. 32/1956) on that matter can no longer be enforced under the current condition. \par \par \uc2  "If the central government does not introduce a better balance of \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  relations with local administrations, resentment towards the central government will grow in a number of provinces and districts," Aberson cautioned. \par \par \uc2  Commenting on Aberson's argument, Fuad said that the adoption of the two laws he proposed on government non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenues and local \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and retributions will pave the way for amending Law No. 32/1956. \par \par \uc2  "The best way to govern \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  relations between the central government and local administrations is through law," Fuad said. (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1996 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011018ds5o002nf\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
