\par\par \b \uc2  STABILITY OF RI'S MACRO- \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMY UNCERTAIN \highlight\uc2  - ECONIT. \b0\par\par\uc2 696 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 June 1996\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1996 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the stability of the Indonesian macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is likely to remain a major issue until the end of year due to a lack of effective measures taken by the government to reduce the country's current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Econit's \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Update, a mid-year review issued yesterday by Indonesian consultants the Econit Advisory Group, said that macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability, which has been clouded by the current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  since last year, is now getting even worse with the government's inconsistent policies aimed at cooling down the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and promoting investment and trade. \par \par \uc2  Econit said in the review that the current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which is estimated to reach US$7.5 billion this year, will continue to threaten macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability. \par \par \uc2  The review said that 1996 should be a year of consolidation both in the macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  sphere and the corporate sector, in a bid to cool the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and to anticipate a foreseeable boom next year. \par \par \uc2  "It will only happen if the monetary policies are in line with \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies, meaning that both should be contractive." \par \par \uc2  "Several monetary policies have been able to cool down the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Some deregulation packages in the real (trade and production) sector, however, fail to support the consolidation process," the review said. \par \par \uc2  "Ironically, the government policies in the real sector, such as the national car program, are contradictory and tend to widen the current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 ." \par \par \uc2  Econit acknowledged that monetary policies, such as the increase of the capital adequacy ratio and reserve requirement of commercial banks, which came into effect last February, as well as the tightening of multi-finance companies' credit expansion, have helped curb credit expansion and increase banks' liquidity since early this year. \par \par \uc2  But the government's 1996/7 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  plan is not counteractive and not supportive of the consolidation process. \par \par \uc2  The review said that the deregulation packages issued by the government in January and June have attracted more foreign investments. Most of the investments do not go to export-oriented projects as expected. it said. \par \par \uc2  The proportion of export-oriented projects among foreign investments declined from 64 percent in 1994 to 57 percent in 1995. During the first quarter of this year, the percentage was recorded at only 43 percent - the lowest figure in the last five years - as compared to 86 percent in the same period of 1994. \par \par \uc2  "The upward trend of foreign investments aimed at the sales of products on the domestic market will widen the current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the future," the review stated. \par \par \uc2  The review also noted that the realization of both domestic and foreign investment plans is very disappointing this year despite a dramatic increase in the amount of investments approved. \par \par \uc2  During the period of Jan.1 to May 15, domestic investment plans rose 145 percent to Rp 59 trillion ($25 billion) over the same period of last year, while foreign investment plans increased by 14 percent to $18 billion. \par \par \uc2  The realization of domestic investment plans in the first 4.5 months of this year, however, was estimated at less than Rp 20 trillion, while the realization of foreign investment plans was less than $5 billion. \par \par \uc2  The low level of realization indicates investors' suspicion of the investment climate in the country due to several discriminative policies as well as inefficient bureaucratic procedures. \par \par \uc2  Econit also pointed out that the increase in the amount of domestic investments is not matched by an increase in the number of investors, as reflected by the number of projects, which increased by only 13 percent for the first 4.5 months of this year. \par \par \uc2  It suggests an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  structure which is dominated by a few groups. \par \par \uc2  On portfolio investment, Econit estimated that the Jakarta Stock Exchange will be stagnant in the second half of this year for several reasons. Most stocks, for example, are now fully-valued, meaning that investors can no longer make capital gains. \par \par \uc2  The widening current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  will also increase investment risks from the macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  point of view. Therefore, investors are likely to shift their funds to other markets which offer lower risks. (alo) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1996 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011018ds6i0033a\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
