\par\par \b \uc2  PRESENT SITUATION HAMPERS EFFICIENCY OF RI  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMY \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 503 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 June 1996\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1996 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , a cumbersome bureaucracy and a lack of transparency in government policies will hamper Indonesia's efforts to increase its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  efficiency when facing tighter competition in the globalization era, a noted economist has said. \par \par \uc2  The managing director of the Institute for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Financial Research, Sjahrir, told a seminar yesterday that effective bureaucracy, transparent policies and legal certainty are prerequisites for Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform should it want to fully enter the free trade era. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia, together with the other members of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations, has been committed to liberalizing its trade by the year 2003. \par \par \uc2  And together with the other member economies of the Asia Pacific \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Cooperation forum, Indonesia is also committed to further liberalizing its trade and investment by the year 2020. \par \par \uc2  Sjahrir told the seminar, which discussed business ethics in the era of globalization, that there have been many complaints of arduous bureaucratic procedures which cause inefficiency. \par \par \uc2  Quoting a neo-classical theory of Milton Friedman, Sjahrir said that too much government interference through the bureaucracy may encourage vested-interest groups to influence the government to create certain regulations favorable for their operation. \par \par \uc2  The government, for example, has issued a new \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the development of a "national car" for the benefit of a single party. \par \par \uc2  In February the government issued a \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  allowing PT Timor Putra Nasional to produce a "national car" in cooperation with Kia Motors Corp. of South Korea. Timor Putra, owned by President Soeharto's son Hutomo Mandala Putra, will enjoy exemption on import duty and luxury sale \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the condition that it can increase the car's local content from 20 percent at the end of the first year of operation to 40 percent at the end of the second year and to 60 percent at the end of the third year. \par \par \uc2  Timor car \par \par \uc2  Earlier this month, the government even allowed Timor Putra to produce its "national" cars at Kia's industrial plant in South Korea with workers and some of components from Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  "Such policies can create rent-seekers and motivate unproductive profit-seekers," said Sjahrir. \par \par \uc2  "An ineffective bureaucracy, coupled with untransparent policies, will become a barrier to improving the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 's efficiency," he said, adding that transparency of policies always requires legal certainty. \par \par \uc2  He reiterated that bureaucratic problems in Indonesia should be solved to support the development of the country's market-oriented \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile another speaker, A. Sonny Keraf of the Atma Jaya University's center for ethics development said that a free market system can guarantee \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  justice. \par \par \uc2  He acknowledged that the free market is not without \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  and free-fight liberalism, but demanded greater fairness and equal opportunities to run businesses. \par \par \uc2  "In the global market system, certain industries surely need protection against overseas competitors but protectionist measures must be objective," he said. \par \par \uc2  He also highlighted the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the "national car" as an example of subjective measures. (kod) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1996 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011018ds6k00385\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
