\par\par \b \uc2  BI ACTS TO COOL DOWN  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMY \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 769 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 September 1996\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1996 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  announced an expansion of the intervention band to 8 percent and a rise in the minimum reserve requirement to 5 percent yesterday in a surprising move to reduce speculative trading and to cool down the overheated \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor J. Soedradjad Djiwandono said that the expansion of the intervention band of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar from 5 percent was necessary to reduce speculative trading in the equity and money markets. \par \par \uc2  Soedradjad explained that the expansion of the intervention band was part of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's policies designed to cool down the overheating \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as well as to strengthen the ability of the money authority to control currency fluctuations. \par \par \uc2  "The move is an important measure to stabilize the overall monetary situation," he told reporters after the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's hearing with House Commission VII for finance and trade. \par \par \uc2  He said that the rapid growth in the financial market over the last five years had not only had a positive impact on the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  but also often caused jittery trading in the money market. \par \par \uc2  The average daily transactions in the rupiah market increased sharply from Rp 400 billion in 1994 to over Rp 1.1 trillion in 1995 and to Rp 20 trillion in June this year. The average daily transactions in the foreign exchange market also jumped from US$2.2 billion in 1994 to more than $5 billion in 1995 and $7 billion in June of this year. \par \par \uc2  "The daily foreign exchange transactions exceeded $14 billion at the end of July," he said. \par \par \uc2  In the capital market, the average daily stock transactions surged from Rp 109 billion in 1994 to Rp 150 billion in 1995 and to more than Rp 269 billion in June. \par \par \uc2  "Non-fundamental factors such as the rioting on July 27 often incited \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the financial market," he said, referring to the unrest which erupted following the storming of the Indonesian Democratic Party's headquarter from its ousted leader Megawati Soekarnoputri. \par \par \uc2  He denied that yesterday's move was launched to counter a worsening of the political situation or the worsening of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals. \par \par \uc2  Foreign \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  Soedradjad said that the foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  held by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  remained at a healthy level of $16.45 billion in July, slightly lower than the $16.48 billion in June. \par \par \uc2  "In addition, we still have a standby loan of $2 billion," he said of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's financial situation. \par \par \uc2  Soedradjad said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's decision to raise the minimum reserve requirement for commercial banks from 3 percent to 5 percent on April 16, 1997, was expected to contain the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  overheating. \par \par \uc2  "The rise in the reserve requirement, the second since February, is necessary to limit the maneuverability of commercial banks," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said that the rise in the reserve requirement from 2 percent to 3 percent in February this year had actually had a positive impact in line with the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's efforts to cool down the overheated \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "But our target has not been achieved. The inflation rate has dropped but we want a much lower rate. The current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  is still under control but we have to prevent it from widening further," he said. \par \par \uc2  Soedradjad said the outstanding loans provided by the country's commercial banks rose by 25 percent in July this year - far higher than the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's 18 percent target for the 1996/97 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year - to Rp 264.55 trillion as of July this year from Rp 211.76 trillion in the same month of 1995. \par \par \uc2  The growth rate of the loans reached 34 percent in the same period, much higher than the 14 percent growth booked by the state-owned banks. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah's value rose sharply against the dollar to 2.326 in early trading on the spot market here yesterday from 2.348 on the previous day, following the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's move to widen the intervention band. \par \par \uc2  The rise in the intervention band allows the rupiah to fluctuate within a range of 192 points or 8 percent. With the rise, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  will only intervene in the market when the dollar trades on the spot market at 4 percent above or below the middle value of its daily conversion rates. \par \par \uc2  However, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's surprising move caused jittery trading on the Jakarta Stock Exchange as foreign investors feared that the rise in the reserve requirement would cause a rise in the inflation rate. (hen) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1996 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011018ds9c005i7\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\pi