\par\par \b \uc2  DEBATE OVER HABIBIE'S CALL ON RATES CONTINUES. \b0\par\par\uc2 731 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 November 1996\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1996 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The debate over State Minister of Research and Technology B.J. Habibie's controversial call to cut \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  continued yesterday, with more economists calling his suggestion an absurd idea. \par \par \uc2  Rizal Ramli, a director of the Econit advisory group, said that Habibie's call to cut annual lending rates gradually to as low as 4 percent is unrealistic. \par \par \uc2  "The appeal to cut the \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to such a low level is quite strange and it could add to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook for 1997," Rizal said while presenting Econit's 1997 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  forecast. \par \par \uc2  Habibie said that Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which might be the highest in the world, should be slashed to as low as 4 percent per annum under what he termed the "zig-zag" mechanism. \par \par \uc2  According to Habibie, the monetary authority should set a target to lower \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to 4 percent, for example, by 2010 when the Asia-Pacific \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Cooperation (APEC) forum's free trade arrangement is fully implemented. \par \par \uc2  In order to meet this target, the monetary authority should start lowering deposit \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to 8 percent per annum from the present rate of 16 percent, he said. \par \par \uc2  Rizal is not alone in his concern. Other economists and banking experts such as Rijanto and Faisal Basrie have also questioned Habibie's monetary hypothesis. \par \par \uc2  The most shocking idea, however, is not Habibie's suggestion on how to reduce \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but his theory about inflation. \par \par \uc2  Habibie - known as 'super minister' because of his close relationship with President Soeharto and his strong influence in shaping the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies - blamed the country's high inflation rates on its high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , according to Habibie, should therefore be reduced in order to cut inflation rates. \par \par \uc2  This notion runs counter to conventional monetary doctrine, which says that lower \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, which in turn incites stronger inflationary pressure on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Rizal said that Habibie's inflationary theory is a new and untested hypothesis. \par \par \uc2  However unusual Habibie's theory about the relationship between \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and inflation, most economists agree that the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  are too high. \par \par \uc2  But economists also say that to cut \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  overnight by more than 3 percentage points is nearly impossible. \par \par \uc2  A single percentage point is of major significance to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Rizal said. If \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  were lowered by 4 percentage points, the cut would incite massive outflows of short-term funds overseas, which in turn would shake Indonesia's monetary system. \par \par \uc2  Deposit rates could be reduced at most by 1 percentage point next year from the present rate of 16 percent, Rizal said. \par \par \uc2  "The cut is possible due to the estimated decline in the inflation rate by 1 percentage point to 7 percent this year," he said. \par \par \uc2  According to data provided by the Far Eastern \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Review, Indonesia's prime (lending) rate is 17 percent per annum, much higher than 2 percent in Singapore, 8.2 percent in Malaysia, 15 percent in Malaysia, and 13 percent in Thailand. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia's real interest rate (the prime rate minus inflation rate) is 10.9 percent, much higher than 0.4 percent in Singapore, 4.9 percent in Malaysia, 6.3 percent in the Philippines and 7.6 percent in Thailand. \par \par \uc2  In other words, the Indonesian banks' interest margin is also much higher than their counterparts in four neighboring countries. \par \par \uc2  Faisal and Rijanto, like Rizal, said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  charged by domestic banks are higher because of their structural problems. \par \par \uc2  "It will, therefore, be difficult for the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to use its power in lowering the rates if the problems in the banking industry are not thoroughly addressed," Rizal said, stressing that local banks are inefficient because of cross-ownership between financial intermediaries and because of high rates of bad loans. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Finance Mar'ie Muhammad declined to comment on Habibie's call to sharply cut the \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  or on his inflation theory. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor J. Soedradjad said Monday that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been working hard to reduce both the country's inflation and \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "We do not only let the \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the market mechanism but also control it through market interventions," he said. He too, declined to comment on Habibie's appeal. (hen) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1996 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011018dsb6000mt\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
