\par\par \b \uc2  LEGAL  \highlight22\uc2 UNCERTAINTY \highlight\uc2  CONCERNS FOREIGN INVESTORS - EXPERT. \b0\par\par\uc2 432 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 November 1996\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  10 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1996 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Foreign investors are more concerned by legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  than any other disincentives to investment, an executive said yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Saiful Haq, \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  division head of Prasetio Utomo Consult accountancy and management consulting company, said foreign investors did not see local income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates as a great disincentive. \par \par \uc2  "They are concerned more with legal certainty than the 30 percent income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rate," Saiful Haq told journalists during a break at Arthur Andersen's Asia Pacific \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and business advisory meeting and seminars here. \par \par \uc2  Arthur Andersen is an international partner of Prasetio Utomo & Co, which manages Prasetio Utomo Consult. \par \par \uc2  Further cuts in income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates will not attract more foreign investors as many other countries offered even higher \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates, Saiful said. \par \par \uc2  Offering privileges to foreign investors may attract foreign capital, but it is meaningless if Indonesia fails to assure foreign investors of legal certainty, he said. \par \par \uc2  He did not elaborate on the country's legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  which, he said, was caused by its legal structure and law enforcement. \par \par \uc2  Another executive at the meeting said it was common knowledge among foreign investors that Indonesia had a bad record in protecting investors. \par \par \uc2  Rulings were often inconsistent, with one department's rulings often differing from another department's, she said. \par \par \uc2  Saiful said that despite some legal infrastructure problems, Indonesia remained attractive to foreign investors. \par \par \uc2  "Many, many foreign investors want to invest here - I know that - considering the size of our market, our \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and our increasing purchasing power," Saiful said. \par \par \uc2  He said every week his company helped prepare about five applications for foreign investment projects for companies from Malaysia, Singapore, Hong Kong, Japan and other countries in the region. \par \par \uc2  "Malaysia's increased investment here is unprecedented, especially in the agro-industry," Saiful said. \par \par \uc2  Foreign investment commitments have increased dramatically in the last four years, from $8 billion in 1992, to $23.7 billion in 1994 and to $39.9 billion in 1995. The government has targeted it would approve $27 billion worth of foreign investment projects this year. \par \par \uc2  John A. Prasetio, president of Prasetio Utomo & Co., said Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals remained sound although there were concerns in some micro-sectors. \par \par \uc2  He forecast that Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  path would not change much despite a projected major reshuffle in the country's political leadership. \par \par \uc2  "Everybody seems to be concerned about a leadership change that might change the direction of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development. However, I believe that any change in the leadership will not bring about many changes in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development," John said. (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1996 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011018dsbj001a2\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
