\par\par \b \uc2  ANNUAL  \highlight22\uc2 BUDGET \highlight\uc2  UNVEILED TODAY. \b0\par\par\uc2 704 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 January 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): President Soeharto is scheduled to propose the 1997/1998 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  today, a \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  most analysts expect to remain austere. \par \par \uc2  Analysts agree that the draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not increase substantially from the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Rp 90.6 trillion (US$38 billion). \par \par \uc2  They contended that the government would continue to tighten \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  liquidity in a bid to cool down \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  overheating. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  overheating is still looming, with widening current account deficits and high inflation rates still haunting the country's macroeconomic management. \par \par \uc2  The expected small increase in the draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the next \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year will most likely be able to stimulate private sector investment and to maintain \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of over 7.1 percent per annum. \par \par \uc2  The President said in his New Year's address that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 's growth declined to 7.8 percent last year, from 8.2 percent recorded in 1995. \par \par \uc2  He said the government's efforts to cool down the overheated \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would push down the inflation rate to 6.7 percent, from 8.6 percent in 1995. \par \par \uc2  This year, Soeharto said, would challenge the government and the private sector alike to achieve high growth without causing overheating. He argued that the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation this year was full of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  To achieve high but sustainable growth, all four factions at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposed late last year that the government raise the 1997/1998 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  by 13 percent over this \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to Rp 102 trillion. \par \par \uc2  The current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which balances at Rp 90.6 trillion, represents a 16.1 percent increase over the previous \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Rp 78.02 trillion. \par \par \uc2  The four factions - the Armed Forces, Golkar, the United Development Party and the Indonesian Democratic Party - used similar assumptions: oil prices remaining at their current levels, continuing inflow of official foreign loans and steadily increasing \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenues. \par \par \uc2  The Armed Forces faction, for instance, projected that Indonesia's crude oil prices would average $16.5 a barrel next \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, receipts from official foreign loans would reach Rp 13.4 trillion and \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenues would rise 12 percent from the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  target of Rp 55.99 trillion. \par \par \uc2  The faction proposed the 1997/1998 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  should be 14.5 percent larger, at Rp 103 trillion, than the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The Golkar faction predicted the government's domestic revenue from oil and gas would increase slightly to Rp 15 trillion for the next financial year, from Rp 14.1 trillion for the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The faction projected domestic revenues from non-oil and gas sectors, including \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  income, would reach Rp 75.6 trillion, up from Rp 64.08 trillion for the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  It proposed the 1997/1998 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  should balance at Rp 102.3 trillion. The proposed \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  increase was to augment the government's increasing routine \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Golkar's chairman, Harmoko, said in Bali last month that his party would press the government to increase the salaries of 4 million civil servants to improve their standard of living so they could serve the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  better. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Finance Mar'ie Muhammad said earlier that even though the government agreed to increase civil servants' salaries, it would not announce it publicly to avoid inflationary effects. \par \par \uc2  The United Development Party faction forecasted that Indonesia's oil prices would average between $17 and $18 a barrel next \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, revenue from official foreign loans would remain at the current level of Rp 12.4 trillion and \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue would increase 20 percent from the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The faction proposed the 1997/1998 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  should balance at Rp 102.7 trillion. \par \par \uc2  The Indonesian Democratic Party faction said the government could further increase \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  receipts because the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  ratio to gross domestic product was lower compared with those of neighboring countries. \par \par \uc2  The faction was therefore optimistic the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the next \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year could balance at Rp 108 trillion, more than 20 percent higher than the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Rp 90.6 trillion. \par \par \uc2  The 1997/1998 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposal will cover the fourth year of the current sixth Five-Year Development Plan period ending in March 1999. (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt160088j\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
