\par\par \b \uc2  GOVT URGED TO INCLUDE  \highlight22\uc2 TARIFF POLICY \highlight\uc2  IN  \highlight22\uc2 BUDGET \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 614 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 January 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The government should include proposed utility charges in the draft state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , members of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  said yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Tadjuddin Noer Said, a member of the House Budgetary Commission from the dominant Golkar faction said such a procedure was important to ensure the tariffing was fair and reasonable. \par \par \uc2  If the charges stated in the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  were approved by the House, the government should not be allowed to change them until the following \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, he said. \par \par \uc2  "If the government plans to adjust the tariffs, it should wait until the next \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  year," he said when commenting on the government's 1997/1998 draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He said that it was now time for the government to adopt such a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to create stability in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and to guarantee that any increases are made for the benefit of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the people. \par \par \uc2  "The government's \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is currently \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Today it announces an increase in telephone charges, for example. Another day it will announce an increase in pure water tariffs, or electricity or maybe fuel oil," he said. \par \par \uc2  "Why doesn't the government integrate these announcements and confine them to when the President unveils the draft state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ?" he suggested. \par \par \uc2  On the country's balance of payments, Hamzah Haz, a member of the Budgetary Commission from the United Development Party, said that the government's decision to focus on reducing the current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  is the right step to take. \par \par \uc2  "The \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  has become a structural problem that needs a comprehensive solution," he said. \par \par \uc2  He cited that most of the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  was contributed by the services sector, particularly transportation. "We need to conduct a comprehensive study of the problem so that we can take the right steps to tackle it," he said. \par \par \uc2  He suggested that the government should further deregulate the shipping sector with a view to reducing the current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the sector. \par \par \uc2  He also criticized the export and import scheme which did not favor Indonesia. "Currently, the export and import scheme is to Indonesia's disadvantage. If we export our products, we can only get payments based on F.O.B (freight on board), but if we import foreign goods we have to pay the costs up to the latest destination," he said. \par \par \uc2  Commenting on the government's rural electrification program in 1997/1998, Iskandar Mandji, a Golkar member of House Commission VI for industry, mining, manpower and investment said that it should be accompanied by an industrialization program in rural areas to prevent villagers becoming too consumerist. \par \par \uc2  Simon P. Morin, a Golkar member of House Commission VII for finance, trade and cooperatives, urged the government not to focus only on the most developed areas in western Indonesia but to expand development activities in the least developed areas in the eastern provinces. \par \par \uc2  "This is one way to arrest the widening \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  gap between the western and eastern parts of Indonesia," he said, adding that besides improving infrastructure, the government should also give special treatment to private investors in the eastern part of Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  A.A. Baramuli, another Golkar member of House Commission VII, said he was concerned about the increase of civil servant \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  from Rp 27 trillion (US$11.6 billion) this \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year to Rp 32 trillion during the next \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year. \par \par \uc2  "The Rp 32 trillion is almost 30 percent of the total state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We're very concerned about this, particularly if we compare it with the development \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Rp 38 trillion. Don't tell me that all the funds will be used for routine \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. (bnt/pwn) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt170089c\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
