\par\par \b \uc2  ELEVATED RAILWAY OR SUBWAY SUITABLE - CITY OFFICIAL. \b0\par\par\uc2 463 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 January 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  3 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): In the midst of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over whether the city will have an elevated railway track or a subway, officials said either would do to start easing Jakarta's traffic woes. \par \par \uc2  Deputy Governor for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Development Affairs Tb. M. Rais said yesterday the Mass Rapid Transit (MRT) project, either elevated or underground, should have started already. \par \par \uc2  Rais could not say whether both would be built. \par \par \uc2  Rais and Governor Surjadi Soedirdja said they could not yet announce the contributions which might help fund the project. \par \par \uc2  The elevated railway track and the subway systems are the two proposed MRT systems from South Jakarta to downtown Kota. \par \par \uc2  An elevated rail would be part of a three layer transport system, comprising rail, turnpikes and regular roads, proposed by the Citra business group, led by businesswoman Siti Hardiyanti Rukmana, who is the President's daughter. \par \par \uc2  The subway is proposed by a study team under the auspices of the Agency for Technology Assessment and Application. \par \par \uc2  The consortium proposing to build it is called the Indonesian Japan European Group. The President's son, Bambang Trihatmodjo joined the consortium in July. \par \par \uc2  City officials and the subway project team's executives have said the subway project can only start after a presidential decree is issued. \par \par \uc2  A \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  works ministry official had said the three layer system does not need a presidential decree. \par \par \uc2  An agreement between the Minister of \b \highlight22\uc2 Public\b0 \highlight\uc2  Works, the Minister of Transportation and the Governor would suffice, Kompas reported yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Citra Group chief executive officer Bambang Soeroso said with an investment of Rp 5.8 trillion the three layer system could start this year. \par \par \uc2  Earlier city officials and representatives from the subway consortium said they could start in April if the presidential decree was issued. \par \par \uc2  On Tuesday the consortium estimated the project would cost Rp 4.5 trillion. \par \par \uc2  Bambang Trihatmodjo was scheduled to sign a memorandum of understanding (MOU) at City Hall yesterday. The MOU was not signed for unclear reason. \par \par \uc2  Despite the time to start the project was fast approaching Surjadi and Rais said it was not time yet to announce how the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  would pay for the project. \par \par \uc2  "We have to be very careful," Surjadi said. "People would immediately reject it if we talked about \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  or fees." The situation could be similar to when toll roads were introduced. \par \par \uc2  People rejected the idea of paying tolls "but now everyone is building toll roads" when the benefits began to show, he said. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile Rais said the city would wait for the new law on \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and fees to come into effect because current \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law was confusing. \par \par \uc2  Both officials and councilors have denied new \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be used to help fund the subway project. (anr) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt19008bf\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
