\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 BANK INDONESIA \highlight\uc2  DEFENDS AGGREGATE TARGETING  \highlight22\uc2 POLICY \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 598 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 January 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor J. Soedradjad Djiwandono defended yesterday the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of targeting monetary aggregates to contain inflation. \par \par \uc2  Soedradjad said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would continue to implement and adjust market-friendly instruments, such as open market operations, discount windows and the reserve requirement, to control the money supply. \par \par \uc2  "Our ultimate goals are low inflation, high growth and a sustainable external balance of payments," Soedradjad told reporters at his office. \par \par \uc2  To achieve these three objectives simultaneously, Soedradjad said, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  must not only control base money (currency) but also influence the money supply in narrow and broad terms. \par \par \uc2  He contended that in an open \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  like Indonesia's the relationship between base and monetary aggregates became uncoupled and their growth became unpredictable. \par \par \uc2  "But please, don't conclude that we are shifting our targeting from base money to monetary aggregates. Base money is our operational target, while monetary aggregates are our intermediate targets to reach our ultimate targets," Soedradjad said, referring to the analysis of Australian economist Ross H. McLeod last week. \par \par \uc2  McLeod told a seminar at the Center for Strategic and International Studies here that targeting monetary aggregates other than base money would be inappropriate because it would not be effective in controlling inflation. \par \par \uc2  Persistent inability to keep inflation within the target of 5 percent per annum had resulted from a failure to sufficiently suppress the growth of base money relative to its demand, McLeod concluded. \par \par \uc2  He said that an unwillingness to acknowledge the pivotal role of base money in determining inflation was leading to the introduction and reintroduction of policies which threatened the achievements of banking deregulation in the 1980s. \par \par \uc2  The policies concerned include credit ceilings through moral suasion and increases in the reserve requirement from 2 percent to 3 percent in February 1995 and to 5 percent next April. \par \par \uc2  Soedradjad argued that McLeod's contention was extremely theoretical and disregarded the realities of Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Doesn't he know that we tightly monitor the development of base money?" Soedradjad asked. "If we do not publicly announce the targeted growth of base money, it does not mean that we do not care about it." \par \par \uc2  He said a steering committee within the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  met weekly to consider \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  developments and monitor the performance of base money in view of projected targets. \par \par \uc2  The meetings, chaired directly by the governor or a managing director responsible for open market operations, discussed open market operations to be undertaken and considered necessary changes to maintain the stability of the foreign exchange rate without undue loss of exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said. \par \par \uc2  In such a globalized \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , full of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Soedradjad noted, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  needed more market friendly instruments to influence market directions. \par \par \uc2  He said his \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of increasing the compulsory reserve requirement for banks was not directly intended to contain inflation but to improve prudential banking practices among local banks. \par \par \uc2  "As a monetary instrument, the reserve requirement is not a substitute for our market operations but it does complement our existing instruments," Soedradjad said. \par \par \uc2  He contended that even countries like the United States still imposed reserve requirements of 10 percent on their banks. And all other countries in Southeast Asia imposed even higher reserve requirements. \par \par \uc2  The governor argued that moral suasion was not a credit ceiling although it was intended to control credit expansions among banks to contain inflation \par \par \uc2  "So, we are pragmatic and eclectic in pursuing and applying our \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , so if we have to err, we err on the safe side," he added. (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt1l00bno\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
