\par\par \b \uc2  GOVT DEFENDS MANAGEMENT OF NON- \highlight22\uc2 TAX \highlight\uc2  REVENUE. \b0\par\par\uc2 592 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 January 1997\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  10 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1997 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Minister of Finance Mar'ie Muhammad yesterday defended the government's handling of non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue raised by ministries and state agencies. \par \par \uc2  Speaking at a \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ' plenary session, Mar'ie acknowledged that the bill on non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue was aimed to improve the government's discipline in managing income raised from sources other than \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "However, it does not mean that we have not been disciplined in implementing our \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  in past years," Mar'ie told reporters after the session. \par \par \uc2  He noted that Soeharto's administration was economically successful because of its budgetary discipline. \par \par \uc2  "With this bill, we hope we can increase non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue from year to year and improve its allocation and management," Mar'ie said. \par \par \uc2  At the previous session, the United Development Party (PPP) demanded that the government provide a full account of the use of non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue since 1969. \par \par \uc2  The PPP contended that many legal levies raised by ministries and state agencies were not included in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and were therefore uncountable. \par \par \uc2  The bill on non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue stipulates that all government income from non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  sources must be accounted for in the annual state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  income is derived from licensing fees, user fees, royalties as well as rents and investment income from state assets. \par \par \uc2  Mar'ie said the bill would serve as a legal basis for the government to raise non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue so that its dependence on foreign funding would continue to decrease. \par \par \uc2  "In a time full of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the financial sector, we should raise funds to the maximum from domestic resources to finance our development. Thus, non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenues will complement our domestic income from \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and oil and gas," Mar'ie said. \par \par \uc2  The state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the 1997/1998 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year balances at Rp 101.08 trillion (US$42.2 billion). \par \par \uc2  The government has projected that non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue would increase 12.9 percent to Rp 8.2 trillion (US$3.4 billion) in the 1997/1998 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  from Rp 7.26 trillion this \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue is expected to increase 15.6 percent to Rp 64.7 trillion in 1997/1998 from Rp 55.98 trillion. \par \par \uc2  The government expects its income from oil and gas to rise only 5.3 percent to Rp 14.87 trillion from Rp 14.12 trillion. And its income from sales of fuel products to fall 69 percent to Rp 249.2 billion from Rp 827.8 billion. \par \par \uc2  "If we expect an increase in our domestic income from the oil and gas sector, it is not realistic because of fluctuating oil prices. \par \par \uc2  "Similarly, it is unrealistic to expect an increase from \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  alone. So, we hope that non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue will help strengthen our domestic income," Mar'ie said. \par \par \uc2  Mar'ie acknowledged there was still room to raise \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue considering that the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  were worth only 11.8 percent of gross domestic product. \par \par \uc2  This rate is the lowest among Southeast Asian countries. \par \par \uc2  The minister noted that the 1997/1998 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  was contractionary in the sense that the funds injected through domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be less than funds taken out in \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue: about a Rp 5.4 trillion contraction. \par \par \uc2  He noted that the 1997/1998 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  was part of the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to maintain macroeconomic stability. "Thus it is expected that the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  will help contain the inflation rate and current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  and help boost \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth." (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1997 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020011001dt1s008iw\par }\par \b \uc2 Search Summary\b0\par \par  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrs \cellx2000\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrs \cellx9072\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Text\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \li50\uc2 (economic or economy) and (uncertain or uncertainty or uncertainties) and (policy or public or tax or taxation or taxes or taxed or spending or expenditure or fiscal or stimulus or budget or deficit or national debt o